 Also they are trying to give people things they've bitched about for years and now find that the EQ developers had a reason for never giving it to you.<br>
 Here's what I've played in the last 2 years besides EQ,<br>
Anarchy Online<br>
DAOC<br>
AC2<br>
SWG<br>
Planetside<br>
<br>
  Out of all of these, I would say SWG was the absolute worst. the combat system and lack of content are horrific.  I was bored in about a week of beta testing.<br>
<br>
DAOC had the most original ideas and best release (even SoE has stolen some of these ideas).<br>
<br>
AO was the most fun and longest lasting for me, it was alot of fun actually but the bugs and lag eventually ruined it for me.  They have come out with an expansion and they've added quite a few things to the original game that make it alot better.  It's worth taking a second look at if you guys are looking for something.<br>
<br>
  EQ is a great game still to this day, alot of people will say its not the game it was, but I think maybe SoE in some cases tried too hard to satisfy all the complainers.  So they've made the game too easy.  Take the transportation system now for instance.   It's great huh?  No timesink but also absolutely no challenges in crossing continents when you are the true newb.<br>
 Thats just one example, I'm sure you all can come up with more.<br>
BUT they've also improved the game in ways nobody ever gives them credit for.<br>
  Take Tradeskills for instance.  Yes its still a boring click fest (even that, they say they are looking at, possibly allowing you to do a stack at a time)but the items you can create now are actually selling for some plat!  And they have good stats!  You've become viable in the market.<br>
 How about the dungeon overhauls?  They've taken some stale, long forgotten dungeons and revamped them into something worthwhile, for FREE even!  They weren't part of the expansions we payed for, and I pay for THOSE willingly because SoE is a business after all and they've always given me my moneys worth., (and yet you will hear people bitch about the expansions also, and why they shouldn't have to pay for them, rofl).<br>
  I've left EQ many, many times to try other games but I've always come back.<br>
  You know why?  Because EQ has given me 4 years of extreme enjoyment and every cent I spent on it has been worth it.  No other game has ever done that for me. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
