<br>
Also, I don't get the arguments about how the changes now stink and are bad for EQ. So what if you can travel around easier and people level faster. This makes the game appeal to a wider base, and the bottom line is MONEY for SoE. For me (full-time job and kids), waiting for a boat was a monumental waste of time. Three weeks to get a level in Guk because of 5 hour corpse runs was a monumental waste of time. It was because of this I quit, and it was because of the improvements with expansions that I have returned. I will never see Time, and I don't care. I don't raid, and I don't care. However, I can still coexist with those who do, and have a good time.<br>
<br>
Back to the orginal post, he was 100% correct. I am not sure why more people do not try and copy EQ, since everything after really bites after the honeymoon is over.<br>
<br>
Gheko, 52 Master<br>
